# Airline Engineer Simulator — Architecture Rules

## Stack
- Browser-only: Vite + TypeScript
- Rendering: Phaser 3 or PixiJS (pixel art, nearest-neighbor scaling)
- Charts: lightweight-charts or Chart.js for time-series UI
- Math model: pure TypeScript in `src/simulation-core/` (no framework imports)

## Separation of Concerns
- `src/simulation-core/` — time-series logic, tick updates, balance formulas (pure functions, Vitest-testable)
- `src/game/` — Phaser/PixiJS scenes: render state only, no business logic
- `src/ui/` — React or DOM panels, charts, HUD
- `src/worker/` — Web Worker for heavy simulation steps (optional)

## Pixel Art
- Sprite sizes: multiples of 8 or 16 (16x16, 32x32)
- No sub-pixel movement for characters
- Export sprites as PNG with transparency
- Phaser texture filter: NEAREST

## Time Series Model
- Prototype in Python via jupyter-kernel MCP, then port to TypeScript
- Use fixed simulation timestep (decouple from frame rate)
- Keep deterministic RNG for reproducible tests
